rComments: Really good teacher but for GER 100 you only get her for half the year.

If you do your homework and come to class, you'll do fine. She is very nice and approachable. She gives good feedback in class which will further help you with your German. The homework really isn't hard and is stuff gone over already in class so sometimes you will already have the answers. No heavy reading or lots of homework. Overall a good prof.
Very good prof at UofT. Very knowledgable and respected.
Yasmin is one of the best profs in the German department. She assigns a lot of readings and makes you participate during class, but she's also very patient, encouraging, and approachable.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: One of the best German profs I've had, she helped me feel more confident in speaking and we worked through some difficult grammar concepts during office hour.
Great teacher! Make sure you do homework and participate, both very important. Don't skip, language is something one has to practise daily.
